name: codecarbon
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "codecarbon" %}
{% set version = "2.1.3" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/codecarbon-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 2de672e8f19dfc4059dfd2ba960e284c8460b689df11356790af08c85bb7e121

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  entry_points:
    - carbonboard = codecarbon.viz.carbonboard:main
    - codecarbon = codecarbon.cli.main:codecarbon
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python
  run:
    - arrow
    - click
    - dash
    - dash-bootstrap-components
    - dash-core-components
    - dash-html-components
    - dash-table
    - fire
    - fuzzywuzzy
    - pandas
    - psutil
    - py-cpuinfo
    - pynvml
    - python >=3.7
    - requests

test:
  imports:
    - codecarbon
    - codecarbon.core
    - codecarbon.external
    - codecarbon.viz
  commands:
    - pip check
    - carbonboard --help
    - codecarbon --help
  requires:
    - pip
outputs:
  - name: codecarbon
  - name: codecarbon-viz
    build:
      noarch: python
    requirements:
      host:
        - python
      run:
        - python >=3.7
        - dash
        - dash-bootstrap-components
        - dash-core-components
        - dash-html-components
        - dash-table
        - fire
        - {{ pin_subpackage('codecarbon', exact=True) }}
  - name: codecarbon-test
    build:
      noarch: python
    requirements:
      host:
        - python
      run:
        - python >=3.7
        - numpy
        - pytest
        - responses
        - requests-mock
        - tox
        - {{ pin_subpackage('codecarbon', exact=True) }}
  - name: codecarbon-dev
    build:
      noarch: python
    requirements:
      host:
        - python
      run:
        - python >=3.7
        - black
        - flake8
        - isort
        - mypy
        - sphinx
        - sphinx-rtd-theme
        - {{ pin_subpackage('codecarbon-test', exact=True) }}
about:
  home: https://pypi.org/project/codecarbon/
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Emissions Tracker
  description: |
    Emissions Tracker is a Python package for tracking the carbon emissions produced by various kinds of computer programs, from straightforward algorithms to deep neural networks.
    By taking into account your computing infrastructure, location, usage and running time, Emissions Tracker can provide an estimate of how much CO2 you produced, and give you some comparisons with common modes of transporation to give you an order of magnitude.
  dev_url: https://github.com/mlco2/codecarbon
  doc_url: https://mlco2.github.io/codecarbon/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - PertuyF
    - benoit-cty
    - Lothiraldan
    - vict0rsch
